s:2516:"<p class="p2&gt;The Regulatory Training Section has created this online course for Authorised Officers to refresh their training.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=">With powers such as these it is essential to remain competent to exercise responsibilities authorised under the <b><a href="http://www.slp.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/main_mrtitle_193_homepage.html" target="_blank">Conservation &amp; Land Management Act (CALM) 1984</a></b> for the <a href="http://www.dpaw.wa.gov.au" target="_blank">Department of Parks and Wildlife</a>. It is also essential to understand any amendments to the CALM Act or Regulations, which will become part of the refresher as they arise. <span style="font-size:14px;">Any employees that are required to have enforcement management responsibilities (cross authorisation) with neighbouring departments must be authorised under the </span><a style="font-size:14px;" href="http://www.slp.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/main_mrtitle_193_homepage.html" target="_blank">CALM Act 1984</a><span style="font-size:14px;"> in the first instance. </span></p>

<p class="p2">This on-line refresher features an assessment relating to an officer's responsibilities under the legislation, and the skills required to carry out this important role. These assessment tests everyday knowledge crucial to being an Authorised Officer, which has been previously provided with your original training. <span style="font-size:14px;">Passing the refresher is essential in retaining your Certificate of Authority and Powers of Enforcement under the </span><b style="font-size:14px;"><a href="http://www.slp.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/main_mrtitle_193_homepage.html" target="_blank">CALM Act 1984</a>, <a href="http://www.slp.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/main_mrtitle_1080_homepage.html" target="_blank">Wildlife Conservation Act 1950</a>, </b><span style="font-size:14px;">and</span><b style="font-size:14px;"> <a href="http://www.slp.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/main_mrtitle_106_homepage.html" target="_blank">Bush Fires Act 1954</a></b><span style="font-size:14px;">. Each student must complete and pass the assessment to complete the refresher. </span></p>

<p class="p2"><br /></p><p class="p2">If you have any further questions or feedback please contact the <b>Regulatory Training Coordinator -</b> Kharis Johnston on 9219 8742. Or <span class="s1"><a href="mailto:regulatorytraining@dpaw.wa.gov.au">regulatorytraining@dpaw.wa.gov.au</a>.</span> </p>";